From e94f77c06588588f487a16d9002f558b57e60c8b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:30:32 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 26/39] WIP: media: dvb-frontends: cxd2878: propagate
 read_status error in cxd2878_tune

The error returned by cxd2878_read_status() was evaluated in an if() but
the body was a bare "ret;" statement with no effect, so the error was
silently dropped (and gcc warned with -Wunused-value). Return ret on
error so the failure is propagated.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
index 2baaa47561da..e9e245aa9481 100644
--- a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
+++ b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/cxd2878.c
@@ -3786,8 +3786,8 @@ static int cxd2878_tune(struct dvb_frontend*fe,bool re_tune,
 	
 	ret = cxd2878_read_status(fe,status);
 	if(ret)
-		ret;
-	
+		return ret;
+
 	if (*status & FE_HAS_LOCK)
 			return 0;
 	
-- 
2.43.0

